1
00:00:11,667 --> 00:00:13,400
Let's come home, Mookie.

2
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:14,400
No, Mommy.

3
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:16,000
Dan, Olive took Mookie!

4
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:18,267
- What? Let's go!
- Let's go! Get in, Emma!

5
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:19,567
Let her go!

6
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:21,500
- Mookie!
- Stop! That's enough!

7
00:00:21,567 --> 00:00:25,700
Mookie!
Give me my daughter back!

8
00:00:25,767 --> 00:00:28,200
You gave Mookie
an animal medication.

9
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:30,433
So I don't think
this is the right time

10
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:31,900
to report to the police.

11
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:36,833
Even though she's hurting me,
it still pains me to leave her.

12
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:39,833
I still can't move my other leg.

13
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,633
I'll be your airplane.

14
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,900
Treat us as your own family.

15
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:47,033
Me, your Uncle Dan, and Mom.

16
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,800
- Hello, Flor?
- Let's meet.

17
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:52,033
I'll give you Mookie's diary.

18
00:01:41,667 --> 00:01:44,033
Olive, I did what you asked.

19
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:46,267
I asked around.

20
00:01:46,333 --> 00:01:48,400
I still couldn't find
where Emma and her family were.

21
00:01:48,467 --> 00:01:51,833
Did you really do
everything you had to do?

22
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,267
Or are you telling me
you're doing something

23
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:56,600
even if you're not?

24
00:01:56,667 --> 00:01:58,767
I swear, Olive,
I'm doing my best.

25
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:01,300
I also talked to a private
investigator.

26
00:02:01,367 --> 00:02:02,667
His name's Greg.

27
00:02:02,733 --> 00:02:05,567
I can ask him to come here
so you can talk to him.

28
00:02:05,633 --> 00:02:06,767
Not now.

29
00:02:08,467 --> 00:02:11,400
There's still someone Mookie
and Emma can turn to

30
00:02:11,467 --> 00:02:12,733
and ask for help.

31
00:02:14,100 --> 00:02:17,100
And that someone might know
where Mookie is.

32
00:02:20,633 --> 00:02:21,533
It's Ma'am Olive.

33
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,267
- Wait.
- What is it?

34
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:28,167
I'm looking for a salon.

35
00:02:28,233 --> 00:02:29,533
I'm going to apply...

36
00:02:29,600 --> 00:02:30,767
Just go with it.

37
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:31,700
Yes, Miss.

38
00:02:31,767 --> 00:02:33,433
- There's a beauty salon...
- Emma?

39
00:02:36,833 --> 00:02:38,167
Please excuse me.

40
00:02:38,233 --> 00:02:40,100
Thank you, Miss.

41
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:43,200
Where's Emma?

42
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:45,600
Ma'am!

43
00:02:45,667 --> 00:02:47,100
Ma'am! You're here.

44
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,900
Are you following me?

45
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:53,267
Miss! Come here for a bit.
Come here!

46
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:55,233
Can I ask a question?

47
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,733
Where's the salon?

48
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,133
Don't act like
you don't know anything.

49
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:03,167
I know you went here
to meet with Emma.

50
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:04,467
Where's Emma?

51
00:03:04,533 --> 00:03:06,967
Oh, Ma'am. Ma'am, no.

52
00:03:07,033 --> 00:03:09,233
I was asking the woman
where the parlor was.

53
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:13,767
Because I will apply for a job.

54
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:17,733
You fired me, remember?

55
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,400
That's why I'm here.

56
00:03:19,467 --> 00:03:21,467
- Really?
- Yes.

57
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,433
Do you really think
you can still convince me

58
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,133
with your lies?

59
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:30,167
Where's Emma?

60
00:03:31,633 --> 00:03:32,767
- Emma?
- Ma'am?

61
00:03:32,833 --> 00:03:34,867
- Emma?
- Ma'am! Ma'am!

62
00:03:34,933 --> 00:03:36,100
- Olive.
- Emma!

63
00:03:36,167 --> 00:03:37,767
- Ma'am!
- Olive.

64
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:40,600
I know you're here
so come out!

65
00:03:40,667 --> 00:03:41,733
Emma!

66
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:44,067
Emma's not here, Ma'am!

67
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:46,500
You don't believe me.

68
00:03:46,567 --> 00:03:48,067
She's not here.

69
00:03:48,133 --> 00:03:48,700
Ma'am...

70
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:50,767
- Ouch!
- I'm sure you know
where Emma is.

71
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:52,467
Ma'am...

72
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:53,833
- Where is she? Tell me!
- Ma'am...

73
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:55,000
I don't know, Ma'am.

74
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,267
I have no idea!

75
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,433
Traitor!

76
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,867
You chose to side with Emma.

77
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:02,267
I know that you know
where she is!

78
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:03,833
I don't know anything, Ma'am.

79
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,700
- Ma'am! Ma'am!
- Aren't you going to tell me?

80
00:04:05,767 --> 00:04:07,667
- Aren't you going to confess?
- Ma'am, you're hurting me.

81
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:10,700
Tell me before you lose
your breath!

82
00:04:10,767 --> 00:04:12,233
- Olive, stop.
- Ma'am, I don't know where...

83
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:15,300
Olive, stop.
We're in a public place.

84
00:04:15,367 --> 00:04:16,800
It looks like Flor really
doesn't know anything.

85
00:04:16,867 --> 00:04:17,533
That's enough.

86
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:22,767
I know you know something
about Emma and Mookie.

87
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:27,100
Brace yourself because
once I find out

88
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,100
you're working with them...

89
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:31,267
I won't leave you alone.

90
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:34,033
You and your family.

91
00:04:49,900 --> 00:04:50,833
Mookie!

92
00:04:53,133 --> 00:04:53,800
Mom!

93
00:04:55,467 --> 00:04:57,100
What happened?

94
00:04:57,167 --> 00:05:00,733
Did Flor give you my diary?

95
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,067
No.

96
00:05:02,167 --> 00:05:04,267
Your mom followed her.

97
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:05,667
She almost saw me.

98
00:05:05,733 --> 00:05:06,200
Oh no.

99
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:10,167
Are you okay?

100
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:11,767
I'm sorry, Mom.

101
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,567
It's not your fault.

102
00:05:13,633 --> 00:05:15,133
I'm glad she couldn't
track us down.

103
00:05:20,367 --> 00:05:23,733
I went to the address
where Flor is, Ma'am.

104
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,800
But she's not there.

105
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:28,667
The neighbors told me
she left in a hurry.

106
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:32,767
Maybe Flor got scared
that's why she got away.

107
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:37,133
Why are you talking
to my daughter?

108
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,767
I'm Zayn, I just got moved
into the neighborhood.

109
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:40,567
Mookie!

110
00:05:41,667 --> 00:05:42,933
Mookie!

111
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,233
- Mookie!
- Mommy!

112
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:46,967
I knew it! This man isn't
a good influence on you.

113
00:05:47,033 --> 00:05:48,033
Mookie!

114
00:05:52,433 --> 00:05:53,267
There's still another person

115
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:54,567
that I want you
to keep an eye on.

116
00:06:55,700 --> 00:06:57,900
I don't like to be drawn
by anyone.

117
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:00,733
It's tiring and it takes
a long time to finish.

118
00:07:00,800 --> 00:07:02,933
I'm also not a fan of selfies.

119
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,900
Promise,
this won't take too long.

120
00:07:06,267 --> 00:07:09,167
And you're too beautiful.

121
00:07:09,233 --> 00:07:10,933
You don't have to flatter me.

122
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,733
Who taught you how to draw?

123
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,600
I bet it's your mom.

124
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:20,033
No.

125
00:07:21,267 --> 00:07:25,667
My mom and I don't
spend time like this.

126
00:07:25,733 --> 00:07:28,233
Oh! Don't be sad.

127
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:30,833
You might ruin your drawing
and make me look ugly.

128
00:07:32,433 --> 00:07:33,900
I need to pee.

129
00:07:33,967 --> 00:07:35,233
Here you go.

130
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:38,100
- Is it done?
- The body isn't fully done yet,

131
00:07:38,167 --> 00:07:39,667
but...

132
00:07:39,733 --> 00:07:43,867
- Can I see it? Let me see.
- You can have a see.

133
00:07:43,933 --> 00:07:45,700
Oh, geez!

134
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:49,533
Why do I look like
Marian Rivera here?

135
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:50,967
Have some snacks first.

136
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:53,100
- Here.
- You're so good.

137
00:07:53,167 --> 00:07:55,067
- Look at it.
- Let me see, Mom.

138
00:07:55,133 --> 00:07:57,467
You're so beautiful here, Mom.

139
00:07:58,600 --> 00:08:00,567
You're very good, Dear.

140
00:08:00,633 --> 00:08:02,867
Thank you.

141
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:03,933
I know, right?

142
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,700
Mom.

143
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:07,167
I'll draw you next.

144
00:08:07,233 --> 00:08:09,267
- Go ahead.
- No need, Mookie.

145
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,067
You're already tired.

146
00:08:10,133 --> 00:08:12,000
Go on and eat. Hurry.

147
00:08:12,067 --> 00:08:13,633
Have some snacks.

148
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:14,733
Okay.

149
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,167
Oh, I know.

150
00:08:16,233 --> 00:08:17,733
Let's just have a selfie.

151
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:20,367
- Come on.
- Selfie?

152
00:08:20,433 --> 00:08:21,500
Okay.

153
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,300
Selfie, my foot.

154
00:08:24,367 --> 00:08:25,433
Where's your phone?

155
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:27,533
There it is. Here it is, Mom.

156
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,133
Thank you, really.

157
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:32,300
It's the first time someone has
done something like this for me.

158
00:08:32,367 --> 00:08:34,133
You do it. You hold this.

159
00:08:41,400 --> 00:08:42,633
Hey.

160
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:43,533
You know what?

161
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:45,867
You look alike.

162
00:08:46,767 --> 00:08:48,233
You can be a mother
and daughter.

163
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:50,733
A mother and child suits you.

164
00:08:51,267 --> 00:08:52,267
Look.

165
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:54,600
This part. The nose.

166
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:57,133
Mom.

167
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,933
This number has been calling
since yesterday.

168
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,033
I don't want to answer it.

169
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:01,967
It might be Ma'am Olive.

170
00:09:02,033 --> 00:09:04,833
Oh, no. Answer it.
It might be an important call.

171
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:07,633
Wait.

172
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:14,033
- Hello?
- I'm glad you answered my call.

173
00:09:14,100 --> 00:09:15,433
This is Zayn.

174
00:09:15,500 --> 00:09:16,433
Zayn?

175
00:09:18,067 --> 00:09:21,833
I saw you when you helped Mookie
escape from Auntie Olive.

176
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,000
How's Mookie?

177
00:09:23,067 --> 00:09:24,667
Can I talk to her?

178
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:31,000
Mom, is that Zayn?

179
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:38,533
Zayn?

180
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:42,300
Mookie! Thank God,
I'm finally talking to you!

181
00:09:42,367 --> 00:09:43,733
I've been calling
since the other day,

182
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:47,267
but Aunt Emma wasn't answering.

183
00:09:47,333 --> 00:09:48,500
How are you?

184
00:09:48,567 --> 00:09:49,500
Where are you?

185
00:09:49,567 --> 00:09:50,767
Can we meet?

186
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,867
Flor called me.

187
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:57,567
We met, and she gave me
your diary.

188
00:09:57,633 --> 00:10:01,200
Let's meet so I can give you
your diary.

189
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:02,500
Really?

190
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:03,567
Sure.

191
00:10:11,067 --> 00:10:15,467
Oh, Zayn, we can't meet.

192
00:10:15,533 --> 00:10:18,033
My mom might see me.

193
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,533
Give me your address then.

194
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,700
I'll go there.

195
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,300
Promise, I'll be careful.

196
00:10:38,267 --> 00:10:43,733
Dear, I know you want
to see Zayn, but...

197
00:10:44,700 --> 00:10:47,667
He's my only friend, Mom.

198
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:51,500
And Zayn is trustworthy.

199
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:55,667
But we're hiding
from your mommy.

200
00:10:55,733 --> 00:10:58,333
What if she traces us
when you meet with Zayn?

201
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:01,467
Just like what happened when I
was supposed to meet with Flor.

202
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:03,133
Your mommy was able
to follow her.

203
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,067
What if that happens again?

204
00:11:05,133 --> 00:11:08,767
Mom, I understand.

205
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:12,133
But I promise you,
we can trust Zayn.

206
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:14,600
I believe that
when we give him our address,

207
00:11:14,667 --> 00:11:18,100
he will never tell Mommy.

208
00:11:18,167 --> 00:11:21,833
He even helped me go
to the police station

209
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:24,167
to see you
when you got detained.

210
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:32,833
Oh, and Mom, Flor wanted
to give me something.

211
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,300
My diary.

212
00:11:34,367 --> 00:11:35,633
What?

213
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,000
Yes.

214
00:11:37,067 --> 00:11:43,400
Flor got scared
when she almost got caught.

215
00:11:44,933 --> 00:11:49,533
That's why she called Zayn
and left my diary to him.

216
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:52,733
Please, Mom.

217
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:56,333
I promise.
Zayn won't tell Mom anything.

218
00:11:56,400 --> 00:12:01,667
I will tell him to be careful
so Mom can't trace us.

219
00:12:04,533 --> 00:12:05,833
Okay.

220
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:07,167
Let's do this instead.

221
00:12:07,233 --> 00:12:09,800
I'll let you meet with Zayn.

222
00:12:09,867 --> 00:12:12,500
But just near our house.

223
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:17,067
I'm not comfortable giving him
our address.

224
00:12:17,167 --> 00:12:18,300
I'll go with you.

225
00:12:18,367 --> 00:12:19,700
I'll watch over you.

226
00:12:21,133 --> 00:12:22,567
Cut that crap!

227
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,467
It's dangerous.

228
00:12:24,533 --> 00:12:26,067
You can't do that!

229
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,667
We're in a very difficult
situation.

230
00:12:30,967 --> 00:12:33,133
And you still want to go out?

231
00:12:42,667 --> 00:12:45,267
Yes, Mookie. I'm on my way
to the place you texted me.

232
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:46,733
I have your diary with me.

233
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,467
Thank you.

234
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:51,233
We're also on our way there.

235
00:12:51,300 --> 00:12:54,867
But make sure
no one's following you.

236
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:56,433
Yes, I got it.

237
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:10,067
Ma'am Olive, it looks like Zayn
will meet with your daughter.

238
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:23,333
Mookie!

239
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:24,200
Zayn!

240
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:28,067
Zayn's here, Mom.

241
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:31,533
This is the first we're going
to see each other again.

242
00:13:34,067 --> 00:13:35,633
You really are a grown-up woman
now.

243
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:37,633
You're blushing. Go on.

244
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:38,733
- Mom.
- Don't take too long.

245
00:13:38,800 --> 00:13:40,033
Come back here real quick, okay?

246
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:44,967
Are you letting Zayn
and I talk alone?

247
00:13:45,967 --> 00:13:47,067
Of course, Dear.

248
00:13:47,733 --> 00:13:50,833
I trust you because
you're a good kid.

249
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:54,000
And I know you won't do
something that will harm you.

250
00:13:54,067 --> 00:13:56,433
- Okay?
- Thank you, Mom.

251
00:13:56,533 --> 00:13:59,033
You really trust me.

252
00:13:59,767 --> 00:14:02,367
I will let you go wherever you
want once we're free to go out.

253
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:06,933
Go on. Make it quick.

254
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,133
Okay, Mom.

255
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,133
I'll keep watch.
Okay.

256
00:14:11,900 --> 00:14:13,067
- Careful.
- Zayn!

257
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:16,267
- Your diary's with me.
- You brought it?

258
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:17,433
Here.

259
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:20,133
- How are you?
- I'm okay.

260
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:21,833
I brought your diary.

261
00:14:21,900 --> 00:14:23,000
Wait, I'll just get it.

262
00:14:23,067 --> 00:14:24,400
Thank you, Zayn.

263
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,267
Thank you.

264
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:30,967
How are you?

265
00:14:31,033 --> 00:14:32,833
- I'm doing okay.
- How about you?

266
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:35,800
- How about you?
- I'm okay, too.

267
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:41,500
- I can see you're having fun.
- Olive?

268
00:14:41,567 --> 00:14:43,300
Why don't you let me join?

269
00:14:43,367 --> 00:14:44,067
Mommy.

270
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:48,400
- Mookie.
- Mom.

271
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:50,367
Oh! Hi, there.

272
00:14:50,433 --> 00:14:53,533
Stealer of someone else's kid.

273
00:15:02,433 --> 00:15:03,667
Let me have my daughter.

274
00:15:04,667 --> 00:15:09,333
I'm her mother,
so I have the right to her.

275
00:15:09,400 --> 00:15:11,600
The right to what?
To hurt her again?

276
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:12,667
To chain her?

277
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:13,933
Lock her up?

278
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:15,867
Treat her like an animal?

279
00:15:15,933 --> 00:15:18,933
You're lucky I haven't called
the cops on you yet.

280
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,433
So let go of my child

281
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:22,800
if you don't want me
to send you back to jail.

282
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:25,667
I will harm even your family.

283
00:15:25,733 --> 00:15:28,267
I still believe that
the truth will come out.

284
00:15:28,333 --> 00:15:29,967
And I'm not scared of you!

285
00:15:31,967 --> 00:15:32,967
Mommy, no, please!

286
00:15:33,033 --> 00:15:34,100
Come on, Mookie.
Let's go home.

287
00:15:34,167 --> 00:15:35,900
Please stop!
You might hurt Mookie!

288
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,200
- What are you doing?
- Please stop!

289
00:15:37,267 --> 00:15:39,267
Who told you to interfere?

290
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,367
- Get out of my way!
- Mommy!

291
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:41,733
Please don't!

292
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:42,467
Zayn!

293
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,067
Give me my daughter!

294
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,800
Mom, what?

295
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,133
Emma and Mookie
went to see Zayn?

296
00:15:52,133 --> 00:15:55,467
I tried to stop them,
but Mookie insisted.

297
00:15:56,133 --> 00:15:57,633
But based on her story,

298
00:15:57,700 --> 00:16:01,267
the young man seemed
trustworthy.

299
00:16:01,333 --> 00:16:03,333
But it's dangerous!

300
00:16:04,433 --> 00:16:07,200
Olive might see them.

301
00:16:07,267 --> 00:16:10,733
It's like letting Mookie get
harmed if I return her to you!

302
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:11,800
Mommy!

303
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:14,000
It's not my habit to take
what's not mine.

304
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:17,800
But God forgive me because
I will protect your daughter.

305
00:16:17,867 --> 00:16:22,000
Let me have your daughter if you
still have mercy left for her.

306
00:16:22,067 --> 00:16:24,233
Over my dead body!

307
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:25,667
I said give me Mookie!

308
00:16:25,733 --> 00:16:27,633
Mookie, come on! Let's go home!

309
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:28,767
I'm begging you!

310
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:30,267
- Get out of my way!
- She's so unlucky

311
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:32,167
to have you as her mother!

312
00:16:32,233 --> 00:16:35,767
If only she could choose,
she would never choose you.

313
00:16:35,833 --> 00:16:37,200
Oh, really?

314
00:16:37,267 --> 00:16:40,400
Mookie is used to sleeping
in a soft bed.

315
00:16:40,467 --> 00:16:42,467
She's used to eating good food.

316
00:16:42,567 --> 00:16:44,600
Can you give her that?

317
00:16:44,667 --> 00:16:46,700
Yes, Mookie likes you now.

318
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:50,067
But once she gets tired
of your stinky house,

319
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:55,533
once she's starving,
I'm sure she'll leave you, too!

320
00:16:56,467 --> 00:16:58,700
Let's go, Mookie. Let's go home.

321
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:00,067
- Stop!
- I said get out of my way!

322
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:00,867
Mookie, let's go.

323
00:17:00,933 --> 00:17:02,333
Yes, we don't have a big house!

324
00:17:03,733 --> 00:17:07,033
Or a soft bed, or good food.

325
00:17:07,100 --> 00:17:10,433
But we have overflowing
love and care.

326
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,200
And we'll shower Mookie with it.

327
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:15,267
We won't hurt her like you do!

328
00:17:15,367 --> 00:17:16,500
Shut up!

329
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:18,500
Mookie! Mookie, let's go!

330
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:20,367
- Mookie!
- Miss Emma, go!

331
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:22,967
- Get out of my way! Mookie!
- I'll take care of her.

332
00:17:23,033 --> 00:17:25,233
Let go of me! Get out of here!

333
00:17:25,300 --> 00:17:26,400
Move!

334
00:17:26,467 --> 00:17:29,667
Mookie! Mookie!

335
00:17:32,433 --> 00:17:38,600
Dear, I know and feel that
it hurts you to see your mom.

336
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,700
Sorry if...

337
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:46,067
I feel this way.

338
00:17:48,533 --> 00:17:50,133
To be honest...

339
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:54,733
I can't understand...

340
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:58,600
what I'm feeling.

341
00:18:02,300 --> 00:18:04,800
Mommy tortured me, right?

342
00:18:07,133 --> 00:18:08,767
But why am I like this?

343
00:18:09,967 --> 00:18:12,033
Why do I feel this way?

344
00:18:12,100 --> 00:18:15,100
Shouldn't I get mad at her?

345
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:20,600
I should get mad at her, right?
But why am I like this?

346
00:18:20,667 --> 00:18:23,100
Why am I hurting?

347
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:26,333
I'm hurting for leaving her.

348
00:18:29,267 --> 00:18:32,033
That's how children are.

349
00:18:32,100 --> 00:18:35,700
They get upset.
They get mad at their mothers.

350
00:18:35,767 --> 00:18:37,733
But they still love them.

351
00:18:39,167 --> 00:18:43,333
But in your case, Dear,
although it hurts,

352
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:46,733
it won't do you any good
if you stay with your mom.

353
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,167
I know that.

354
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,400
I feel sorry for my mom.

355
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:05,267
But...

356
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:11,500
I know that if I come home...

357
00:19:13,567 --> 00:19:17,600
she will only repeat everything
she did to me.

358
00:19:21,433 --> 00:19:24,667
I really think Mommy is sick.

359
00:19:24,733 --> 00:19:29,633
I watched a case like hers
in the United States.

360
00:19:29,733 --> 00:19:34,067
She's making me sick even if
I'm perfectly healthy.

361
00:19:34,133 --> 00:19:37,067
A mother is accused
of medical child abuse,

362
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:40,867
also known as Munchausen
Syndrome by Proxy.

363
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:44,300
Oh, that! I told you about that!

364
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:45,667
I saw something like that, too.

365
00:19:45,733 --> 00:19:47,667
Right?

366
00:19:47,733 --> 00:19:49,233
- The one on the television?
- I told you guys about it.

367
00:19:49,300 --> 00:19:50,767
I knew it.

368
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:54,067
Olive is mentally ill.

369
00:19:54,133 --> 00:19:57,167
It's a solid proof against her.

370
00:19:57,233 --> 00:19:58,467
Send her to jail.

371
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:01,367
If not in prison,
in a mental facility.

372
00:20:01,433 --> 00:20:03,333
She must get checked.

373
00:20:03,433 --> 00:20:04,567
Right!

374
00:20:04,633 --> 00:20:05,500
How about you?

375
00:20:06,467 --> 00:20:08,733
Don't you want to tell
the police about it?

376
00:20:10,233 --> 00:20:12,467
What will happen to Mommy?

377
00:20:12,533 --> 00:20:13,500
Will she go to jail?

378
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:14,800
Yes!

379
00:20:14,867 --> 00:20:16,433
I don't want her to go to jail.

380
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:20,267
I don't think I can bear
seeing her imprisoned.

381
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:21,367
We're going to lose.

382
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:23,333
Mookie.

383
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,367
Okay, listen.

384
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:27,467
Don't worry about that for now.

385
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:32,667
But let us consult
what we should do about you.

386
00:20:32,733 --> 00:20:36,300
Because we can't hide you
for a long time.

387
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:39,300
In the eyes of the law, I can't
take you away from your parent.

388
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:46,767
I'm really sorry, Mom.

389
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:48,900
I'm sorry.

390
00:20:51,367 --> 00:20:54,533
I'm sorry for dragging you
into my problems.

391
00:20:54,600 --> 00:21:00,400
Sorry for being a burden to you.

392
00:21:00,467 --> 00:21:04,433
Dear,
you don't have to apologize.

393
00:21:04,500 --> 00:21:06,000
We wanted this.

394
00:21:06,067 --> 00:21:09,500
We wanted to care
and protect you.

395
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:13,000
And we're just being cautious
with our moves.

396
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,833
To make sure you're safe.

397
00:21:18,533 --> 00:21:21,267
And don't ever think
you're a burden to us, okay?

398
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:23,033
Because that's not true.

399
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:39,700
After everything I did
for Mookie...

400
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,767
she still went with Emma!

401
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:48,567
She chose other people
over her own mother!

402
00:21:51,267 --> 00:21:52,633
And Emma...

403
00:21:54,467 --> 00:21:56,900
has really taken my child
away from me.

404
00:21:58,633 --> 00:22:00,667
They're monsters!

405
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:03,200
Ungrateful beasts!

406
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:05,933
- Olive.
- Beasts!

407
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,200
I won't stop!

408
00:22:09,267 --> 00:22:12,633
I will get even with them!

409
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:14,333
I will exact revenge!

410
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:17,133
- Olive, stop.
- I won't leave them alone.

411
00:22:17,233 --> 00:22:18,967
I will find them.

412
00:22:19,033 --> 00:22:21,400
I will make sure
to get even with them!

413
00:22:22,100 --> 00:22:24,767
I'm still waiting at the hotel
where Kayla's kidnapper stayed.

414
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,033
I'm hoping she'll come back.

415
00:22:28,100 --> 00:22:29,700
But I haven't seen her again.

416
00:22:30,267 --> 00:22:31,467
I'm sorry, Danilo.

417
00:22:31,533 --> 00:22:34,700
Oh, come on.
You've helped us a lot already.

418
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,300
But don't worry, Bro.

419
00:22:36,367 --> 00:22:38,867
I'll still go there
whenever I'm free.

420
00:22:38,933 --> 00:22:43,533
And when I see her, I'll follow
her wherever she goes.

421
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:46,133
Who knows, I might see Kayla.

422
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:51,867
But how do I know if ever
it's Kayla?

423
00:22:58,867 --> 00:23:00,967
Kayla has only one mark.

424
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:04,200
The heart-shaped birthmark
on her thigh.

425
00:23:13,067 --> 00:23:13,100
The clothes Uncle Danilo bought
for you fit you.

426
00:23:16,733 --> 00:23:20,000
You've been wearing
the same clothes for days.

427
00:23:20,067 --> 00:23:24,767
I'm ashamed that you had
to spend money on me.

428
00:23:24,867 --> 00:23:27,867
It's okay.
Those clothes are affordable.

429
00:23:28,933 --> 00:23:30,200
Oh, Mom!

430
00:23:30,267 --> 00:23:33,100
It's okay. Can I wipe myself?

431
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:34,100
I can do it on my own.

432
00:23:34,167 --> 00:23:35,967
What you did for me is more than
enough.

433
00:23:36,033 --> 00:23:38,933
You helped me clean up
these past few days.

434
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,000
But your legs aren't
fully healed yet, right?

435
00:23:41,067 --> 00:23:42,767
How is it?
Do you still feel any pain?

436
00:23:45,167 --> 00:23:46,933
I'm feeling okay now, Mom.

437
00:23:47,933 --> 00:23:51,433
You know, I'm grateful

438
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:55,933
because my mom can't inject any
more medicines into me.

439
00:23:57,933 --> 00:24:03,800
I'm also grateful because
you're there to encourage me.

440
00:24:03,867 --> 00:24:05,800
You don't have to flatter me.

441
00:24:05,867 --> 00:24:09,567
I'm telling the truth, Mom.

442
00:24:09,633 --> 00:24:15,833
That's why I thank you,
Daddy Danilo, and Miss Ligaya.

443
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:20,300
Because you're all there for me.

444
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:21,767
And...

445
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:25,833
I really wish
you were my family.

446
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:27,333
And you were my mom.

447
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:33,800
Oh, gosh.

448
00:24:36,067 --> 00:24:37,900
You don't have to cry.

449
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:43,300
Let me take care of you if
you want me to be your mother.

450
00:24:44,333 --> 00:24:45,733
All right.

451
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:47,033
I'll give you a sponge bath now.

452
00:24:48,033 --> 00:24:49,700
Give me your legs.

453
00:24:55,167 --> 00:24:56,167
Does it hurt?

454
00:24:57,067 --> 00:24:58,067
No?

455
00:25:15,233 --> 00:25:16,567
Olive, what are you doing?

456
00:25:16,633 --> 00:25:18,600
I'm going live on social media.

457
00:25:18,667 --> 00:25:22,367
When did she give birth to
Mookie if she lost a child?

458
00:25:22,433 --> 00:25:25,933
All I know is that Ma'am Olive
never had a husband.

459
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,733
This woman is a kidnapper!

460
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:31,867
And she mercilessly kidnapped
my daughter!

461
00:25:31,933 --> 00:25:33,967
That woman is unbelievable!

462
00:25:34,033 --> 00:25:37,133
Emma, she's telling everyone
that you're a kidnapper!

463
00:25:37,233 --> 00:25:39,967
Bro, remember the night
of the landslide?

464
00:25:40,033 --> 00:25:41,500
She's that woman.

465
00:25:41,567 --> 00:25:43,500
She's the woman
who took your child.

466
00:25:43,567 --> 00:25:44,733
Emma should know about this.

467
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,300
Let's go!

468
00:25:46,367 --> 00:25:47,833
What are you doing?

469
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:49,900
I'm not done yet!
Why did you stop it?

470
00:25:49,967 --> 00:25:51,933
Olive, enough!

471
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:53,767
You're only going
to harm yourself.

472
00:25:53,833 --> 00:25:55,100
I don't care!

473
00:25:56,133 --> 00:26:00,667
What's important to me right now
is to get Mookie back from Emma.
